"Kennedy" is a news panel show hosted by Kennedy Montgomery. Kennedy Montgomery is a libertarian that you may recognize from 90's MTV, Stossel, and the Independents.

JEDIDIAH BILA is in the studio to replace Kennedy for the night. No monologue.

Tonight's panel consists of REMY MUNASIFI, WILL RAHN, JIMMY FAILLA. First topic - Jeb Bush and his presidential aspirations.  They discuss a poll trying to figure out which presidential candidate Americans would like to take on vacation. At the top - Hillary. Also at the bottom.. Hillary. Weird.

The panel returns to talks bout Rachel Dolezal and being transracial.

JEFF CORWIN is in studio to talk shark attacks via phone.

The panel returns to discuss a crazy women who helps break out prisoners. Next up, is Shakesphere outdated or essential? Guide put out by Janet Napolitano is being used in the University of California to police language.  Among the bad things, calling America a "melting pot" and saying that people are "articulate". Among many other things.

KYLE SMITH is in the studio to talk about an article he wrote claiming that women don't understand Goodfellas.  Jedidiah & DEE DEE SORVINO take him on.

Nightcap: 100 year old women says key to her longevity is lots of beer. Have at it!
